# Hermes Bridge — example crontab entry.
# Install with: crontab -e   (paste the line in)

# Heartbeat/logging only — safe to run as often as you like, never consumes
# the shared read cursor for this identity:
*/5 * * * * /path/to/examples/cron-heartbeat.sh

# Want the full default/active "radio" polling protocol instead (5-min idle,
# 30-sec during a live conversation)? Plain cron can't go below 1-minute
# granularity, so that needs a systemd --user timer, not cron — see
# radio-poll.sh, radio-poll.service, radio-poll.timer, and the setup steps
# in README.md.
